  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nWhen using a mono repo structure in which the `node_modules` directory is at the root of the repo, truffle is not able to resolve Solidity imports for packages placed in the root `node_modules`.\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\nI don't have an example repo yet, but it is easy to see why this happens in [truffle-resolver](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-resolver/blob/develop/npm.js#L28)\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nWhen doing something like `import \"openzeppelin-solidity/contracts/...`, truffle should use the same module resolution spec as node (if the package is not in `./node_modules`, search for modules in the parent directory and so on)\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Truffle version: 4.1.9\r\n* node version: 9.11.1\r\n* npm version: 6.0.1\r\n\r\nIf this is the desired behavior, maybe an option could be included in the `truffle.js` file to specify additional paths to look for imported contracts.",
