    "body": "Yes this is a good suggestion. There's actually some code to do this in a different context at `truffle-require` [here](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle-require/blob/develop/require.js#L45-L78) and agree it makes sense that `truffle-resolver` should behave this way.\r\n\r\n@vdrg We have been looking at lerna a bit here so quite curious about it. Some questions:\r\n+ what does your project structure look like? Do you have multiple contract packages that consume the same set of dependencies hoisted to the root directory?\r\n+ is it required that the dependencies sit in the root? Are their drawbacks to packages maintaining their own node_modules?",
