    "body": "That is correct, we have multiple contract packages. Currently we are using lerna + yarn workspaces, which hoists absolutely everything to the root directory. What we are doing for now is using the `nohoist` option for yarn so that it doesn't hoist the specified packages: it creates a symlink for packages in the repo and for external packages it just copies them into the `node_modules` dir of each package.\r\n\r\nTbh maybe this is not really necessary :sweat_smile: as it can be \"fixed\" by doing what I described before. The only drawbacks of using `nohoist` is that you have to manually specify which packages you don't want to hoist and for external packages the code gets copied multiple times.",
